Commit Message: Initial commit
Add travis
Add initial package structure
No need to specify linux dist on travis anymore; test osx and windows too
Travis update: python not available on osx/windows
Add work-in-progress tracking beam files
Replace old TB script by WIP new one, ignore pycharm directory through gitignore
Add FITS reader
Style fix
Add code to calculate TAB indices
Add FITS writing code; ignore VerifyWarning in FITSreader
Committed wrong file
Add option to disable progress bars, fix implicit drop of unit when saving time steps
Fix reverted disable/enable of progress bar
Remove name tags from logger
Make sure TAB loaded from disk have correct dimensions
Allow usage of --cb if --taskid is not specified
Add test for tools.py
Fix name of editorconfig file
Fix str to Time conversion
Add tests for tracking_beam.py
Add pytest and coverage to travis
Add codecov badge
Install pytest-cov on travis
Add explicit unit conversion to test
Add init file to test folder"
Allow python 3.8 to fail tests for now
Add tests for create_tracking_beam (todo: main function)
Add test data
Add tests for FITS reader, and fixed bug in writing weights/scales/offsets columns
Add test for main module of create_tracking_beam
Disable codecov comment bot unless there are changes in coverage
Add README to package long description
Fix typo in travis file; add explicit linux dist to avoid travis warning
Use python 3.8-dev on travis
Fix potential issue with negative Dec on command line
test negative Dec
Update README, remove matplotlib dependency
Add citation files, add metadata, update version
Fix typo in setup.py
Add badges
Add automatic deploy to pypi
baselines have to be set only once, move to __init__
Add functionaliy to calculate TAB indices for a vector of time steps
Use vectorized TrackingBeam by default
update version
Require numpy >= 1.17
Add script to create synthesised beam; Add support to unpack bits to fits_reader
Add SB tool to readme
Update version
Replace travis by github actions
Fix github action pip
Add Github action badge
Disable GHA for docs and deploy for now
Add tutorials
Point to tutorials in README
Only deploy docs on master branch / tags
Fix numpy deprecation warning in creating rotation matrix. As a bonus this also creates one big Quantity object so no more need to do that manually
Fix calculation of tab indices when time is array. Fixes #5
Style fix
Update version
Update email
Update email in docs
